The paper deals with a graph problem related to planarity, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves finding a set of vertices to delete in order to obtain a planar graph, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm used in the paper involves reducing the input graph and using techniques for graphs of bounded treewidth, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents a simpler algorithm for a problem that has been previously solved using deep results, which is a topic in algorithms and complexity (cs.SI).
